<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5270804>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. 11Nesonotus vulneratus Hugel, n. sp. 1, head (frontal view). 2, head and pronotum (dorsal view). 3, right T1 outer view. 4, male left FW, anal field. 5, male right FW, anal field. 6, stridulatory file, SEM, ventral view. 7, male terminalia, ventral view. 8, male terminalia left side view. 9, male right circus, SEM, inner ¾ side view. 10, female terminalia, ventral view. 11, female terminalia, left side view. 6, 9 are scan electron microscope pictures. Scale bars: 6, 9: 1 mm; others: 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5270804/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5270806>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12–15. Oscillogram of the calling song of Nesonotus vulneratus Hugel, n. sp. in natura. 13–15 are details of 12 (arrows). Martinique, Le Morne Rouge, 2.VIII.2008, 22h00, 25°C." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5270806/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

